Windows Registry Acquisition & Analysis Tools

KAPE (Kroll Artifact Parser and Extractor)
	•	Purpose: Live data acquisition and triage
	•	Use: Quickly collect registry hives and forensic artifacts from a live system
	•	Features:
	•	Fast targeted data collection
	•	CLI and GUI support
	•	Useful for incident response

Autopsy
	•	Purpose: Digital forensics analysis (GUI-based)
	•	Use: Extract registry files from disk images or live data sources
	•	Features:
	•	User-friendly interface
	•	File system navigation and extraction
	•	Supports multiple data sources

FTK Imager
	•	Purpose: Data acquisition and file extraction
	•	Use: Mount disk images or access live systems to export registry files
	•	Features:
	•	Mount and browse disk images
	•	Export registry hives
	•	“Obtain Protected Files” for live systems
	•	Limitation: Does not extract Amcache.hve

