Registry Analysis Tools

Registry Viewer (AccessData)
	•	Purpose: View extracted registry hives
	•	Use: Open and analyze registry hives similar to Windows Registry Editor
	•	Features:
	•	Familiar UI (similar to regedit)
	•	Simple hive navigation
	•	Limitations:
	•	Loads only one hive at a time
	•	Does not process transaction logs

Registry Explorer (Eric Zimmerman)
	•	Purpose: Advanced registry analysis
	•	Use: Analyze multiple registry hives with enhanced accuracy
	•	Features:
	•	Load multiple hives simultaneously
	•	Incorporates transaction logs for updated data
	•	Bookmark feature for commonly investigated keys
	•	Part of a DFIR-focused toolset

RegRipper
	•	Purpose: Automated registry data extraction
	•	Use: Generate reports from registry hives
	•	Features:
	•	Extracts data from important forensic keys/values
	•	Outputs results in structured text reports
	•	Available in CLI and GUI
	•	Limitation:
	•	Does not process transaction logs
	•	Best used after merging logs (e.g., with Registry Explorer)

⸻

Note
	•	Registry Editor cannot load exported hives
	•	Use dedicated tools for accurate offline analysis
	•	Combining tools (e.g., Registry Explorer + RegRipper) improves results